Description: Name of the server as it appears in the client server browser
Long form description of the server when clicked on in the client server browser
If enabled, server will appear in the client server browser
Password required to connect to the server (except for whitelisted players). Default is no password
Category of the server shown when clients first select a new game
Max number of connections allowed on at one time (negative is infinite)
Internal server IP-address the server should bind to. Default is Any (all IPs on the host)
Internal server IP-address the RCON server should bind to. Default is Any (all IPs on the host)

Max active players, 0 = Unrestricted. Setting this gives your match score a boost in the server browser when you have fewer players than needed, and an extra boost if players have recently abandoned. (This affects your server score only and is not limiting amount of total users that can connect).
The address of a Discord Server used for players on this world.
If enabled, UPnP will be enabled on the server. Requires a UPnP-enabled router to work
If enabled, allows beta branches (branches other than "public") to be installed. Specify the branch under "Selected Beta Branch". NOTE: Update the server after switching branches!

[Beta branch](https://steamdb.info/app/739590/depots/) to install. Requires "Enable Beta Branch" to be enabled. Set any required password under "Beta Password". NOTE: Update the server after switching branches!
Multiplier applied to the cost of learning a specialty. Values below 1 decrease speciality cost, above 1 increase speciality cost.
Multiplier applied to the rate of skill points gained over time. Values below 1 decrease the rate, above 1 increase the rate.
Factors into experience per level specialties. Default is 25, higher values increase experience requirement, lower values reduce it.
Multiplier applied to crafting resource cost. Values below 1 decrease crafting resource cost, above 1 increase resource cost.
Multiplier applied to crafting time. Values below 1 decrease crafting time, above 1 increase crafting time.
Percentage to refund the player when they remove a specialty.
Percentage of speciality experience that is also gained as level experience. Not recommended for public servers. Default is 0.0
Multiplier applied to item max stack size. Values below 1 decrease max size, above 1 increases max size. A server restart is required for correct calculation.
Multiplier applied to item weight. Values below 1 decrease item weight, above 1 increase item weight. A server restart is required for correct calculation.
Multiplier applied to fuel yield per unit. Values below 1 decrease yield, above 1 increase yield. A Server restart is required for correct calculation.
Global scale for how quick plants mature.
Multiplier applied to storage connection range. Values below 1 decrease range, above 1 increases range. A server restart is required for correct calculation.
Endgame crafting cost presets for Laser and Computer Lab. Does not affect work orders in progress.
Adjusts the default shelf life of all foods, with higher values causing food to last longer. For example, setting to 2 double the shelf life while setting to 0.5 halves the shelf life.
Max hours a user can play per day. After their allotted time, they can still play but not expand calories with work. 0 means no limit.
Remaining playtime can be added to the next day.
If Rollover Daily Playtime is true then this is the maximum hours playtime in a day. This limits how much playtime player can save up by not playing.
Whether or not a meteor exists in the world.
Time in days when the meteor will impact. Changing this value will override impact time for current active meteor.
Allows players to rent access to a given deed from another when enabled.
When enable, players will be able to use voice chat.
When enabled, the variety of food you ear will provide a bonus.
When enabled each player has unique preferences for each type of food that yields a bonus, and periodic 'cravings' will emerge for an additional bonus.
The World will be on Pause if this option is set.
The World will resume as soon as first player login to the world.
If set, rooms can have empty blocks serve as windows and still count as room.
Repeated rooms earn this multiple value of the previous ones. This makes duplicate rooms less valuable in a house.
Specifies how many wall blocks are required to make one empty window or door block without penalty. It counts all wall blocks in the room, including window blocks itself.
Can players fast forward time by sleeping in a bed? If all online players sleep, time will accelerate. (This shouldn't be enabled for public servers!).
The max time multiplier that will pass while sleeping. Lower this to make the simulation fast-forward more reliably.

DisplayName: Time To Reach Maximum Time Rate
Description: How long it takes to reach the max sleep time. Makes for a smooth transition into sleeping.

Determines whether overthrowing a government is allowed or not. If set, then a constitution with higher house value than the current can be ratified. Setting this to true also makes it impossible to make laws about placing or crafting a constitution.
To overthrow an existing government, a constitution must be placed in a building that exceeds the previous constitution's value by this percent. 100 = 100%
The 'Active Players' demographic will check this many of the past days to determine the hours played by a user.

DisplayName: Hours Played To Be Active Demographic
Description: The 'Active Players' demographic will apply to any users who played this many hours within the past number of days specified above.

DisplayName: Percent Of Days To Be Active For Long Term Demographic
Description: Percent of days a user needs to be considered active (as determined by other property) to be in the 'Long Term demographic'. 1 = 100%
The 'Abandoned Players' demographic will check this many past days for hours played by the user.

DisplayName: Hours Played To Be Abandoned Demographic
Description: The 'Abandoned Players' demographic will apply to any users who have not played more than this many hours in within the past number of days specified above.
The 'Abandoned Players' demographic will only apply to users who have a citizen age greater than this many hours.
Demographics are updated after this much time has passed.

DisplayName: Allow Invalid Civic Container Time In Minutes
Description: How much time can a civics object have an invalid or missing host object before it goes invalid?
Recurring transfers like rent and wages are paid after this many minutes.

DisplayName: Allow Laws To Prevent Login Or Play
Description: Can laws prevent someone from logging in or playing? Enable with caution: users can create a law that blocks everyone from logging in if this is enabled.
After this many hours, the election will end with or without a winner.

DisplayName: Minimum Percent of Eligible Voters Required
Description: The election will not produce a winner unless this percentage of eligible voters have cast their vote.

DisplayName: Minimum Days Between Elections of This Type
Description: Once an election of this type completes, another of the same type cannot be started for this many days.

DisplayName: End Election Early When This Percent Have Voted
Description: If this percentage of voters have cast their vote, then the election will end early (but not sooner than the Minimum Election Time).

DisplayName: Percent Of All Voters To Instant Win
Description: If this percent of *all possible voters* votes yes, the election will instant-finish.

DisplayName: Percent Of All Voters To Instant Lose
Description: If this percent of *all possible voters* votes no, the election will instant-fail.
Should the way a citizen votes be hidden?
The percent value a vote from a twitch viewer counts relative to vote from a player.
The maximum percent contribution all combined Twitch voters can have in election.
Name of the save to load at startup.
How often to write changed data to disk, in seconds.
If true, removes failed to load objects upon loading.
Path for storage (Leave as 'Storage' for default settings).
Path to file to start game from for a New World, if blank (null) then World will be generated.
Defines the announcement countdown intervals in minutes. The second countdown is handled by the CountdownStart setting. (-1 - disabled)
Specifies the message to be sent when the automatic restart auto shutdown occurs.
Specifies how many seconds until the shutdown counter starts.
The currently selected language. If you change languages, you'll need to restart the server for the changes to fully take effect.
Determines how much of any CPU core can be used by the server. Defaults to 25%, and should supposedly not be set higher than 75%.
An experimental feature that allows parallel (as opposed to sequential) world object ticks. May increase performance at the cost of stability.
Game progress time advances at this rate.
Minimum distance between trees. Lower values can impact performance negatively.
The default experience gain for all players, regardless of their other sources of experience points and difficulty settings.
Scales skill penalty to suffocation. (0 to disable).
Scales how much time of day matches real time. Higher numbers result in shorter day/night cycles (as a value of X seconds per real-world second), but will not affect simulation speed.

Maximum number of tooltip parts stored in server's cache. Lowering this number can reduce RAM usage, but may impact response time for user's tooltip request. Changing this setting will take effect after server restart.

Web Server URL. If not specified then remote IP address will be used. Usually you should ignore it, but if you want to use DNS name or hide web server behind a proxy (for SSL or friendly name then it may be useful. Users default port if not explicit port specified (HTTP - 80, HTTPS - 443). Format: http(s)://myserver.com:[port]
Rate at which the server updates to clients, per second. Default is 20 Seconds

The user account associated with this server. This is public knowledge and shared with clients. Setting this will allow achievements earned by players on this server to be visible in other servers (as well as future features to come). Visit [play.eco](https://play.eco/) to link your steam account or create a new account.
Password for the SLG Account
